
@startuml
' Sober Taxi System Class Diagram

class Customer {
  - id: int
  - name: String
  - email: String
  - phoneNumber: String
  - numberOfRideShares: int
}

class CarOwner {
  - id: int
  - name: String
  - contactInfo: String
  - carRegistrationNumber: String
}

class SelfDrivingCar {
  - id: int
  - licensePlate: String
  - model: String
  - status: String (available, inUse, maintenance)
  - lastMaintenanceDate: Date
  - damageAmount: double
  - accidentHistory: List<Accident>
}

class Accident {
  - id: int
  - date: Date
  - location: String
  - damageAmount: double
}

class RideHailingService {
  - id: int
  - pickupTime: DateTime
  - dropoffTime: DateTime
  - pickupLocation: String
  - dropoffLocation: String
  - duration: int
  - distance: double
  - passengers: int
  - fee: double
  - requestType: String (App, HandWave)
  - leadCustomer: Customer
}

class RideSharingService {
  - id: int
  - pickupTime: DateTime
  - dropoffTime: DateTime
  - pickupLocation: String
  - dropoffLocation: String
  - duration: int
  - distance: double
  - negotiatedFee: double
  - customers: List<Customer>
}

class Request {
  - id: int
  - type: String (RideHailing, RideSharing)
  - status: String (Pending, Confirmed, Completed)
}

class AppRequest {
  - requestId: int
  - customerId: int
}

class HandWaveRequest {
  - requestId: int
  - detectedBy: String (CameraSystem)
}

class SoberApp {
  - version: String
  - users: List<Customer>
}

class ImageRecognitionSystem {
  - systemId: int
  - accuracyRate: double
  - requestsDetected: List<HandWaveRequest>
}

class AdminPanel {
  - adminId: int
  - managedCars: List<SelfDrivingCar>
  - managedAccidents: List<Accident>
}

' Associations
Customer "1" --> "0..*" RideHailingService : uses
Customer "1" --> "0..*" RideSharingService : participates in
Customer "1" --> "0..*" Request : makes
CarOwner "1" --> "1" SelfDrivingCar : owns
SelfDrivingCar "1" --> "0..*" Accident : has
RideHailingService "1" --> "1" Request : corresponds to
RideSharingService "1" --> "1" Request : corresponds to
Request "1" --> "0..1" AppRequest : is an
Request "1" --> "0..1" HandWaveRequest : is an
HandWaveRequest "1" --> "1" ImageRecognitionSystem : detected by
AdminPanel "1" --> "0..*" SelfDrivingCar : manages
AdminPanel "1" --> "0..*" Accident : manages
SoberApp "1" --> "0..*" Customer : registered users
SoberApp "1" --> "0..*" Request : handles
@enduml

---

### 📌 Notes:

- **Customer** can be both a **lead customer** in a ride-hailing service or a participant in a ride-sharing service.
- **RideHailingService** and **RideSharingService** are types of **Request**.
- **Request** can be further categorized into **AppRequest** or **HandWaveRequest**.
- **ImageRecognitionSystem** detects **HandWaveRequests**.
- **AdminPanel** is used to manage cars and accidents.
- **SelfDrivingCar** can have multiple **Accidents** in its history.
- **RideSharingService** allows up to 10 passengers, while **RideHailingService** allows up to 6.

